com.googlecode.cqengine.query.comparative

Class LongestPrefix<O,A extends CharSequence>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.query.comparative.SimpleComparativeQuery<O,A>
      • com.googlecode.cqengine.query.comparative.LongestPrefix<O,A>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComparativeQuery<O,A>, Query<O>

    public class LongestPrefix<O,A extends CharSequence>
extends SimpleComparativeQuery<O,A>
    LongestPrefix queries are used to find the longest prefix in a dataset for a given query term. Given a data set with the following records 
     | id | code   | Operator  |
 | 0  | 35387  | Foo       |
 | 1  | 35385  | Bar       |
 | 2  | 353855 | A.N.Other |
    A longest prefix query using a query as shown below would return the entity with id 0

    Query<Foo> query1 = longestPrefix(Foo.CODE, "35387123456"));

    Author:
    Glen Lockhart
